programme.title: Trato hecho - T3, E11: Colección de baquetas firmadas / Coche Trans Am...
programme.desc: Paul recibe un Trans Am GTA de 1988, famoso por películas como Los locos del Cannonball y Los caraduras. Cindy consigue una colección de baquetas firmadas y le cuesta mucho deshacerse de ella.

programme.title: Trato hecho - T3, E12: Artículos de cultura pop / Coche de carreras de...
programme.desc: Paul comprueba en el terreno si merece la pena subastar un coche de carreras utilizado en el remake de 2011 de Footloose. Los hermanos Garrett traen una colección de artículos de la cultura pop.

programme.title: Trato hecho - T3, E13: Cañón / Calíope

programme.title: Trato hecho - T3, E14: Taburete motorizado / Espada confederada

programme.title: El precio de la historia - T25, E02: Eres un buen hombre, Chumlee Russell
programme.desc: El prototipo de una figurita de lucha libre llega a la tienda. Más tarde, Rick intenta hacerse con una pistola pistola-cuchillo del siglo XIX. Y, por último, Chum celebra la Navidad antes de tiempo.

programme.title: El precio de la historia - T23, E10: La musa de Chum
programme.desc: Traen a la tienda un sombrero de vaquero muy especial que perteneció a Ronald Reagan. ¿Podrá Rick echarle el lazo a la prenda?

programme.title: El precio de la historia - T23, E11: El submarino amarillo
programme.desc: Una invasión británica llega a la tienda cuando les traen un póster de la película ‘Yellow submarine’, de los Beatles. ¿No podrá Chum con tanta psicodelia o disfrutará del viaje en busca del acuerdo?

programme.title: El precio de la historia - T23, E12: Flamencos en el jardín

programme.desc: De vuelta en Montebello, Gunter se presenta para ‘ayudar’ a Rene, que le ignora por completo. Darrell trata de hacer de Kimber su reina, mientras Ivy y sus chicos se abren paso con fuerza para alcanzar el éxito.

programme.title: Restauradores - T6, E04: Mantener el control

programme.title: 100 Women
programme.desc: From building herself a reputation as a rebellious star in the 1990s to being made a dame by King Charles in 2024, Tracey Emin is an icon in the contemporary art world. With a career spanning over three decades, her pieces tackle issues of sex, pain and the female experience in a deliberately confessional way. But Emin's life hasn't always been filled with awards and royal recognition. Over the past few years, she has survived an aggressive cancer, opened an art school and produced paintings and sculptures with renewed intensity. Twenty-five years after her famous installation My Bed was nominated for a Turner Prize and first exhibited in London, the artist sat down with BBC 100 Women to talk about the person behind the artwork and the legacy she hopes to leave behind.

programme.title: Slumdog Millionaire
programme.desc: An uneducated teenager from the Mumbai slums is only one question away from winning a quiz show, but the authorities are reluctant to believe a youngster from such a humble background could succeed without cheating. Under questioning, he tells a police inspector the eventful story of his life - and how he came to know so much. Danny Boyle's Oscar-winning drama, starring Dev Patel and Freida Pinto

programme.title: Turner & Hooch
programme.desc: A Californian detective investigating the murder of a local man by drug smugglers has only one witness to help him solve the case - the large, smelly dog that belonged to the victim, which is about to turn the detective's well-ordered existence into chaos. Family comedy, starring Tom Hanks, Mare Winningham and Craig T Nelson

programme.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
programme.desc: An electrical repairman sees a fleet of UFOs and develops an increasing fascination with mountain-shaped forms, driving his wife to despair. Meanwhile, a single mother has a similar fixation after her son mysteriously vanishes, and a team of scientists investigates a series of strange events around the world. Eventually, they are all drawn to a mountain where aliens are about to make contact. Steven Spielberg's sci-fi drama, starring Richard Dreyfuss, Francois Truffaut and the late Teri Garr

programme.title: Clear and Present Danger
programme.desc: A CIA analyst gets caught up in the Colombian drug trade while trying to track down terrorists responsible for the murder of a close friend of the US president - but his investigations point to illegal activity and corruption at the very top of government. Action thriller, based on Tom Clancy's novel, with Harrison Ford reprising his role from Patriot Games alongside Willem Dafoe, Anne Archer and James Earl Jones

programme.title: Deep Impact
programme.desc: A TV reporter investigating a presidential misdemeanour stumbles on evidence that a comet is on a collision course with Earth, threatening the future of the human race. Meanwhile, an astronaut prepares to lead his crew on a do-or-die mission to intercept the danger. Sci-fi drama, starring Robert Duvall, Tea Leoni, Morgan Freeman and Elijah Wood

programme.title: The Electrical Life of Louis Wain: Interview Special
programme.desc: Stars Benedict Cumberbatch and Claire Foy talk about making director Will Sharpe's eccentric biopic of artist and inventor Louis Wain

programme.title: London Has Fallen
programme.desc: World leaders gather in London for the funeral of the British Prime Minister, unaware they have been led into a trap. A terrorist plans to kill them all, and devastate the city, and the only people in a position to stop him are the President of the United States and the indomitable head of his secret service. Action thriller sequel to Olympus Has Fallen, starring Gerard Butler, Aaron Eckhart and Morgan Freeman

programme.title: Arkansas
programme.desc: Kyle and Swin live by the orders of a drug kingpin called Frog, who they have never met. When a deal goes horribly wrong, the consequences are deadly. Thriller, starring Liam Hemsworth, John Malkovich and Clark Duke, who also co-wrote and directed

programme.title: Sweet Country
programme.desc: An aged Aboriginal farmhand shoots a white man in self defence and goes on the run as a posse gathers to hunt him down. Australian period drama, starring Hamilton Morris, Bryan Brown and Sam Neill

programme.title: BSL Zone: Sign2Win
programme.desc: BSL Zone's first deaf gameshow. Three teams have their BSL language and deaf cultural knowledge tested with a prize of £1000 going to the winner

programme.title: Journey to the Center of the Earth
programme.desc: An explorer discovers a prehistoric monster-infested world deep beneath Earth's crust and faces a tough ordeal escaping the predatory attacks of the creatures as he tries to guide his team back to safety. Sci-fi adventure based on Jules Verne's novel, starring Pat Boone, James Mason, Arlene Dahl and Diane Baker

programme.title: The 300 Spartans
programme.desc: The ruler of the Persian empire vows to expand his realm by conquering Greece. The king of Sparta steps forward to defend his homeland and the other kingdoms of Greece, but when he is betrayed by a political council, he finds himself without an army and must fend off the vast invading army with a mere 300 warriors. Historical drama, starring Richard Egan, Ralph Richardson and Diane Baker

programme.title: Tora! Tora! Tora!
programme.desc: Fact-based Second World War drama recounting the bombing of Pearl Harbour from both the Japanese and American perspectives, reconstructing the events leading up to the devastating attack on the US naval base in 1941. Starring Martin Balsam, So Yamamura, Joseph Cotten, James Whitmore and Jason Robards

programme.title: The Eagle
programme.desc: A Roman centurion seeks to restore his father's honour by recovering the standard of a legion that disappeared. Accompanied by his British slave, he makes a dangerous journey north of Hadrian's Wall into the Scottish Highlands, territory occupied by hostile tribes. Action adventure, starring Channing Tatum, Jamie Bell, Mark Strong and Donald Sutherland

programme.title: Fisherman's Friends: One and All
programme.desc: Following the success of their first album, the Fisherman's Friends struggle to adjust to their new-found fame and work towards a second album. Comedy sequel, starring James Purefoy, Sam Swainsbury and Dave Johns

programme.title: Antwone Fisher
programme.desc: A troubled Navy recruit is prone to violent outbursts and is ordered to see a psychiatrist, who gradually helps the mentally scarred sailor to come to terms with his past and abusive childhood. Fact-based drama, directed by and starring Denzel Washington. With Derek Luke, Joy Bryant and Salli Richardson

programme.title: Patti Cake$
programme.desc: Aspiring rapper Patricia Dombrowski lives a dead-end day in a dead-end New Jersey town. However, she is determined not to let life keep her down as she, her best friend Jheri and a growing band of misfits look to make their hip-hop dreams come true. Drama, starring Danielle Macdonald, Sahr Ngaujah and Bridget Everett

programme.title: The Moonraker
programme.desc: A foppish royalist nobleman leads a double life as a Roundhead-baiting highwayman. However, after Cromwell's final victory at the battle of Worcester, the dashing hero has to smuggle the son of Charles I to safety in France. Swashbuckling adventure, starring George Baker, Sylvia Syms, Marius Goring, John Le Mesurier and Patrick Troughton

programme.title: The Desert Fox
programme.desc: German commander Rommel falls out of favour with Hitler following his defeat at El Alamein. On returning to his homeland, he is torn between his oath of loyalty and lack of faith in the Fuehrer's unstable leadership, prompting him to become involved in an assassination plot. Second World War drama, starring James Mason, Jessica Tandy, Cedric Hardwicke, Leo G Carroll and Luther Adler

programme.title: Hangman's Knot
programme.desc: Confederate soldiers wipe out a group of Union troops carrying a shipment of gold, but later learn the Civil War ended the month before, rendering their attack a criminal act. The soldiers go on the run with the loot, but their worries deepen when they are besieged by bandits. Western, starring Randolph Scott, Donna Reed, Lee Marvin and Richard Denning.

programme.title: A Kid for Two Farthings
programme.desc: A six-year-old boy from London's East End is fascinated by the stories of an elderly neighbour, who tells him about the strange powers of the mythical unicorn. The lad sets out to find such a magical beast, only to encounter a single-horned goat. Certain he has found the creature he was looking for, he takes it home - and sets about trying to make wishes come true. Drama, with Jonathan Ashmore, Celia Johnson, Diana Dors and David Kossoff

programme.title: We Live in Time Interview Special
programme.desc: Stars Andrew Garfield and Florence Pugh - along with director John Crowley - talk about making the Film4-backed romantic drama We Live in Time

programme.title: Midway
programme.desc: The story of the Battle of Midway, a clash between the American fleet and the Imperial Japanese Navy, which marked a pivotal turning point in the Pacific Theatre during the Second World War. When US intelligence intercepts messages detailing a Japanese attack on an unnamed location, it becomes a race against time to both figure out where will be hit next and how to prepare for an impending battle. Roland Emmerich's drama, starring Ed Skrein, Patrick Wilson, Woody Harrelson and Luke Evans

programme.title: The Electrical Life of Louis Wain: Interview Special
programme.desc: Stars Benedict Cumberbatch and Claire Foy talk about making director Will Sharpe's eccentric biopic of artist and inventor Louis Wain

programme.title: Smile
programme.desc: Dr Rose Cotter works in the emergency psychiatric unit of a busy hospital, tending to troubled patients including a new arrival, Laura Weaver. After witnessing a traumatic incident involving Laura, Rose becomes convinced she is being threatened by an uncanny entity. Horror, starring Sosie Bacon, Kyle Gallner and Jessie T Usher

programme.title: Not Okay
programme.desc: An ambitious but misguided young woman desperate for friends and fame fakes a visit to Paris to upscale her social media presence. A terrifying incident takes place in the real world, which becomes a part of the imaginary trip and offers all the material she wants. After posing as a survivor of a deadly attack, she soon learns that online notoriety comes with a price. Comedy drama, starring Zoe Deutch and Mia Isaac

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Part 1 of 5. Cobra attacks a G.I. Joe convoy and steals a high-powered experimental laser to complete their latest weapon... the weather dominator. When the Joes launch an air assault, Destro uses the device, and it's stormy skies ahead for the Joe team.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Part 2 of 5. The Joe team uses an energy mirror array to counter Cobra's Weather Dominator attack on Washington, D.C. When their defense is successful, the Weather Dominator explodes in orbit, scattering its vital components across the globe.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Part 3 of 5. The Joe team is preparing to trek across the globe to the Island of no return to retrieve one of the three fragments of the weather dominator before Destro and Cobra can get their hands on it.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: Battle on the Roof of the World
programme.desc: Part 4 of 5. As the Island of no return battle rages on, Spirit goes one-on-one with Storm Shadow for the second weather dominator fragment. Meanwhile, in the freezing arctic battleground, both sides fight for the final fragment of the weather dominator.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Part 5 of 5. As the weather dominator device is reassembled at Cobra's Temple, it's up to the Jor team's full-scale assault on the base to prevent the world from falling into Cobra's grasp!

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: The Further Adventures Of G.I. Joe - Day 1
programme.desc: Cobra seizes control of the G.I. Joe space shuttle, using the shuttle and a series of relay cubes to create a pyramid-like “zone” no vehicle or machine can function in.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: The Further Adventures Of G.I. Joe - Day 2 : Rendez Vous In The City Of The Dead
programme.desc: Shipwreck and Snake Eyes continue to evade capture in an effort to get back to the Joe team with vital data about Cobra's control cubes.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: The Further Adventures Of G.I. Joe - Day 3 : Three Cubes To Darkness
programme.desc: As three of Cobra's relay cubes are activated, Cobra commander moves forward with his plans to activate the fourth and final cube in the sea of lost souls. Meanwhile, Shipwreck and Snake Eyes escape Cobra's troopers in Enterprise City.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: The Further Adventures Of G.I. Joe - Day 4 : Chaos In The Sea Of Lost Souls
programme.desc: Cobra commander activates the pyramid of darkness, stranding not only the JOES but also his comrades the crimson twins. Always prepared with a backup plan, Tomax and Xamot have other designs for the pyramid and Cobra.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.sub-title: The Further Adventures Of G.I. Joe - Day 5 : Knotting Cobra's Coils
programme.desc: Chaos ensues as the leaders of Cobra struggle for control of the pyramid of darkness. As Cobra forces battle each other, the Joe team is able to regain control of space station delta and launch a full-scale assault to try to destroy the Pyramid.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: When a secret military satellite is forced out of orbit by Cobra, the Joe team races to its location before Cobra can get their hands on it. But both the Joes and Cobra find that a third party has entered the battle for the device.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: In a diabolical plan to control the world's fuel supplies, Cobra begins detonating oil tankers and pipelines by remote. But when sparks uncovers the frequency Cobra is using to destroy the tankers, the Joe team may be able to turn the tables on them!

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Cobra plots to attack the cities of the world with lava flow when they kidnap Dr. Shakur and bring him to their jungle base, planning to use his breakthrough technology to harness the energy of Earth's core and cause volcanic eruptions.

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Cobra schemes to use the animals of the world against humanity with a mind-control signal enabling them to make any animal do their bidding, and the device causes Junkyard to turn on the Joes. Can they defeat Cobra and get Junkyard back to normal?

programme.title: GI Joe: A Real American Hero
programme.desc: Flint, Bazooka, and the others have to fight their way through a deadly Cobra temple to reach a group of brilliant scientists whom Cobra has kidnapped. As the Joes try to navigate the deadly maze, they find there is nothing fun about this funhouse!

999: On the Front Line
programme.desc: A night out ends badly when a young man is involved in a fight. A patient who has diabetes collapses with blood sugar levels that the paramedics say are as the highest they've ever seen. Paramedics suspect the barking cough of a toddler is the classic sign of croup, and an intoxicated man with a deep gash to his head needs stitches but first, they need to wrestle a bottle of alcohol from his grasp

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: This edition focuses on a mother's role in different family units. Jacob, 20, arrives in resus with suspected internal bleeding after crashing his car into a wall at high speed, while Joan, 82, is treated for a head wound after tripping down the stairs at home, and seven-year-old Jackson has a suspected infection on his cheek. Documentary following life inside the A&E department of St George's in south-west London, focusing on patients, their families and the staff dealing with the emergencies

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: Samuel, 24, is rushed to A&E after crashing his motorbike and being thrown into the road, while two-year-old Florence is brought in by her mum and dad, who suspect that she has swallowed a coin. Documentary following life inside the A&E department of St George's in south-west London, focusing on patients, their families and the staff

programme.title: Food Unwrapped

Kate Quilton looks at the growing trend of hemp-based food products

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces

programme.title: Ugly House to Lovely House with George Clarke
programme.desc: Back in 2017, George drafted in architect Chris Mason to help Wendy and Allan, whose Colchester home resembled a block of flats. They ended up with an enormous double-height extension and a Roman-style portico, but the ambitious scheme blew their budget and the project remained unfinished. George returns to find out whether they have managed to finish the property to the same exceptional standards

programme.title: George Clarke's Old House, New Home
programme.desc: George tackles two very different properties from the Georgian architectural period. Later, he travels to the Peak District, where he comes across a farmhouse which is in desperate need of a transformation

programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: Friends - T9, E19: El del sueño de Rachel

programme.title: Friends - T9, E21: El del test de fertilidad

programme.title: Friends - T9, E22: El del donante
